------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Welcome to the Miriad ftp area at the Australia Telescope National Facility
                 ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Miriad is a radio-astronomy data reduction package used at the ATNF to process
aperture-synthesis observations, primarily from the Australia Telescope
Compact Array (ATCA) at Narrabri.

This directory contains distribution tar files for installation from source
code and also binary installations for selected platforms.

  DISCLAIMER		    -- Standard GPL legal disclaimer.
  INSTALL.html		    -- Installation instructions (included in
			       miriad-common.tar.gz).
  README		    -- This file.

Installation from source code is based on GNU autoconf/make using the
following two tar files:

  miriad-code.tar.gz	    -- Miriad source code.
  miriad-common.tar.gz	    -- Common runtime files, including installation
			       instructions and compiled documentation.

For a binary installation you need miriad-common.tar.gz and one of the
following tar files:

  miriad-darwin_x86.tar.gz  -- Binaries for Intel Macs (Mac OS X 10.4.8,
			         Darwin 8.8.1, gfortran 4.2.0, gcc 4.2.0).
  miriad-linux.tar.gz	    -- Binaries for 32-bit Linux systems (Linux
			         2.4.18-1-686-smp, g77 3.2.3, gcc 3.2.3).
  miriad-linux64.tar.gz	    -- Binaries for 64-bit Linux systems (Linux
			         2.6.8-11-amd64-k8-smp, g77 3.3.5, gcc 3.3.5).
  miriad-sun4sol.tar.gz	    -- Binaries for Sun Solaris systems (SunOS 5.6,
			         Sun WS6U2 f77 5.3, cc 5.3).

If you are interested in recent changes:

  miriad-rcs.tar.gz	    -- Miriad RCS version files.

The following subdirectories contain additional material:

  tutorials		    -- Overheads from data reduction symposia.
  updates		    -- Incremental source code updates.

For convenience, the User and Programmer Guides contained in
miriad-common.tar.gz are available separately:

  userguide.ps.gz	    -- Miriad User Guide, A4 paper.
  userguide_US.ps.gz	    --   do. for US letter size paper.
  progguide.ps.gz	    -- Miriad Programmer Guide, A4 paper.
  progguide_US.ps.gz	    --   do. for US letter size paper.

Enquiries may be addressed to miriad@atnf.csiro.au

